CatDescriptText: Mr. Kenneth Deyempert, 9552 Lysle Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 21, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that the proposed six-day-a-week school attendance, as proposed by Governor Leader, is the answer to the Russian challenge in scientific education?" answer reads: "No, I don't think that six days a week is going to make any child learn better. A youngster has to take up what he wants and then set his mind to it."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Kenneth Deyempert, wearing striped shirt, varsity letterman jacket with "W", name patch reading "Ken", and basketball pin, standing in front of wall with poster with image of a duck and a marlin that reads "The Gill N' Quill.... Lounge"
